<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>£3,500/mo Roadmap — Dual Audience Strategy</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Barlow+Condensed:wght@600;700;800&family=Nunito+Sans:wght@300;400;600;700&family=Fira+Code:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #0d0f12;
    --surface: #12151a;
    --card: #171b22;
    --border: #1f2530;
    --border2: #2a3240;
    --orange: #ff6b2b;
    --orange-dim: #7a3010;
    --teal: #2bcfb1;
    --yellow: #f5c842;
    --red: #ff4d4d;
    --green: #3dd68c;
    --blue: #4d9fff;
    --text: #96a3b5;
    --white: #e8ecf2;
    --muted: #404d5e;
  }

  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

  body {
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: 'Nunito Sans', sans-serif;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  /* Diagonal stripe accent top */
  .top-bar {
    height: 4px;
    background: repeating-linear-gradient(
      90deg,
      var(--orange) 0px, var(--orange) 40px,
      var(--teal) 40px, var(--teal) 80px
    );
  }

  .wrap {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 52px 24px 100px;
  }

  /* ── HEADER ── */
  .header {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
    animation: up 0.5s ease both;
  }

  .mono {
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--orange);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .mono::after { content: ''; flex: 1; max-width: 60px; height: 1px; background: var(--orange); opacity: 0.4; }

  h1 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(48px, 7vw, 82px);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 0.96;
    color: var(--white);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  h1 .hl { color: var(--orange); }
  h1 .dim { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.65em; }

  .header-sub {
    font-size: 14.5px;
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 560px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--orange);
    padding-left: 16px;
  }

  /* ── TRUTH BOX ── */
  .truth {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    animation: up 0.5s 0.08s ease both;
  }

  .truth-card {
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 22px 24px;
  }

  .truth-card.bad {
    background: rgba(255,77,77,0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,77,77,0.2);
  }

  .truth-card.good {
    background: rgba(61,214,140,0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(61,214,140,0.2);
  }

  .truth-label {
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .bad .truth-label { color: var(--red); }
  .good .truth-label { color: var(--green); }

  .truth-title {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .truth-body {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* ── DUAL AUDIENCE ── */
  .dual {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    animation: up 0.5s 0.12s ease both;
  }

  .aud-card {
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .aud-header {
    padding: 14px 20px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .aud-header.fighter { background: rgba(255,107,43,0.1); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,107,43,0.2); }
  .aud-header.athlete { background: rgba(43,207,177,0.08); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(43,207,177,0.2); }

  .aud-icon { font-size: 20px; }

  .aud-name {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .aud-role {
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-left: auto;
  }

  .fighter .aud-role { color: var(--orange); }
  .athlete .aud-role { color: var(--teal); }

  .aud-body { padding: 18px 20px; }

  .aud-row {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    padding: 7px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 12.5px;
  }

  .aud-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .aud-key { color: var(--muted); }
  .aud-val { color: var(--white); font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; }
  .aud-val.pay { color: var(--green); }
  .aud-val.low { color: var(--red); }
  .aud-val.mid { color: var(--yellow); }

  /* ── REVENUE MODEL ── */
  .rev-section {
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    animation: up 0.5s 0.16s ease both;
  }

  .rev-section-header {
    padding: 16px 24px;
    background: var(--surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .rev-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
  }

  .rev-item {
    padding: 20px 22px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
    position: relative;
  }

  .rev-item:last-child { border-right: none; }

  .rev-who {
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .rev-item:nth-child(1) .rev-who { color: var(--teal); }
  .rev-item:nth-child(2) .rev-who { color: var(--orange); }
  .rev-item:nth-child(3) .rev-who { color: var(--blue); }

  .rev-product {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 17px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .rev-desc { font-size: 11.5px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px; }

  .rev-math {
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .rev-subtotal {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--green);
  }

  .rev-footer {
    padding: 16px 24px;
    background: var(--surface);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .rev-note { font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); }
  .rev-total-big {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 36px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--green);
  }

  /* ── LEAD GEN ── */
  .leadgen {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 28px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    animation: up 0.5s 0.2s ease both;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 26px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .section-sub {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .channels {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 14px;
  }

  .channel {
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 16px 18px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .channel:hover { border-color: var(--border2); }

  .ch-top {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .ch-icon {
    width: 32px; height: 32px;
    border-radius: 7px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    font-size: 15px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ch-icon.ig { background: rgba(255,107,43,0.12); }
  .ch-icon.li { background: rgba(77,159,255,0.12); }
  .ch-icon.ref { background: rgba(61,214,140,0.1); }
  .ch-icon.yt { background: rgba(245,200,66,0.1); }

  .ch-name {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .ch-tag {
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-left: auto;
  }

  .ch-tag.hot { color: var(--orange); }
  .ch-tag.new { color: var(--teal); }
  .ch-tag.warm { color: var(--green); }

  .ch-body { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.55; }
  .ch-body strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }

  /* ── PHASES ── */
  .phases-label {
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    animation: up 0.5s 0.24s ease both;
  }

  .phases { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; }

  .phase { animation: up 0.5s ease both; }
  .phase:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0.28s; }
  .phase:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.36s; }
  .phase:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.44s; }
  .phase:nth-child(4) { animation-delay: 0.52s; }

  .phase-hdr {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    cursor: pointer;
    user-select: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .phase-hdr:hover { border-color: var(--border2); }
  .phase-hdr.open { border-radius: 8px 8px 0 0; border-color: var(--border2); }

  .ph-n {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 700;
    width: 28px; height: 28px;
    background: var(--orange);
    color: var(--bg);
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ph-i { flex: 1; }

  .ph-when {
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--orange-dim);
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }

  .ph-title {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .ph-rev {
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--green);
    background: rgba(61,214,140,0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(61,214,140,0.18);
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .ph-chev { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; transition: transform 0.3s; }
  .phase-hdr.open .ph-chev { transform: rotate(180deg); }

  .phase-body {
    display: none;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border2);
    border-top: none;
    border-radius: 0 0 8px 8px;
  }

  .phase-body.open { display: block; }

  .task {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 38px 1fr auto;
    gap: 12px;
    align-items: start;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }

  .task:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .task:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.012); }
  .task.done .task-copy { opacity: 0.28; text-decoration: line-through; }

  .cb {
    width: 20px; height: 20px;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--border2);
    border-radius: 4px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .cb:hover { border-color: var(--orange); }
  .cb.ticked { background: var(--orange); border-color: var(--orange); }
  .cb.ticked::after { content: '✓'; font-size: 11px; color: var(--bg); font-weight: 800; }

  .task-copy strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 13.5px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 3px;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .task-copy span {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .badge {
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 3px 7px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    white-space: nowrap;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  .b-fire { background: rgba(255,77,77,0.1); color: var(--red); border: 1px solid rgba(255,77,77,0.2); }
  .b-rev { background: rgba(61,214,140,0.08); color: var(--green); border: 1px solid rgba(61,214,140,0.18); }
  .b-lead { background: rgba(43,207,177,0.08); color: var(--teal); border: 1px solid rgba(43,207,177,0.18); }
  .b-sys { background: rgba(255,107,43,0.08); color: var(--orange); border: 1px solid rgba(255,107,43,0.18); }
  .b-cont { background: rgba(77,159,255,0.08); color: var(--blue); border: 1px solid rgba(77,159,255,0.18); }

  /* Progress */
  .prog-wrap {
    margin-top: 36px;
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    animation: up 0.5s 0.6s ease both;
  }

  .prog-meta {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .prog-meta span { color: var(--orange); }

  .track { height: 4px; background: var(--border); border-radius: 2px; overflow: hidden; }

  .fill {
    height: 100%;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--orange-dim), var(--orange));
    border-radius: 2px;
    width: 0%;
    transition: width 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.25,1,0.5,1);
  }

  @keyframes up {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(14px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .truth, .dual, .rev-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .task { grid-template-columns: 34px 1fr; }
    .badge { display: none; }
    .ph-rev { display: none; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="top-bar"></div>
<div class="wrap">

  <!-- Header -->
  <div class="header">
    <div class="mono">Dual Audience Strategy · £3,500/mo by July</div>
    <h1>FIGHTERS <span class="dim">build the brand.</span><br><span class="hl">ATHLETES</span> PAY THE BILLS.</h1>
    <p class="header-sub">Your combat sports audience gives you credibility and reach. But your revenue comes from higher-income athletes who <em>aspire</em> to train like fighters. This roadmap uses both — without abandoning either.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Truth -->
  <div class="truth">
    <div class="truth-card bad">
      <div class="truth-label">✕ Why it hasn't worked</div>
      <div class="truth-title">Fighters are a credibility audience, not a buying audience</div>
      <div class="truth-body">Most of your 60k are hobbyist/amateur fighters earning under £30k/yr. After gym fees, fight camps and gear — there's simply nothing left. You're not failing to sell. You're selling to the wrong room.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="truth-card good">
      <div class="truth-label">✓ What actually works</div>
      <div class="truth-title">Use fighter credibility to attract athletes who CAN pay</div>
      <div class="truth-body">Rugby players, footballers, cyclists, and ex-sport 30-somethings <em>admire</em> the fighter aesthetic. They want that conditioning. They earn £35k–£70k+. They already spend on performance. And your combat background makes you the most interesting S&C coach in the room.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Dual Audience -->
  <div style="font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:14px;animation:up 0.5s 0.1s ease both;">▸ Your Two Audiences — Different Roles</div>
  <div class="dual">
    <div class="aud-card">
      <div class="aud-header fighter">
        <div class="aud-icon">🥊</div>
        <div class="aud-name">Combat Athletes</div>
        <div class="aud-role">Brand Engine</div>
      </div>
      <div class="aud-body">
        <div class="aud-row"><span class="aud-key">Role</span><span class="aud-val">Credibility + Content</span></div>
        <div class="aud-row"><span class="aud-key">Willingness to pay</span><span class="aud-val low">£0–£150 max</span></div>
        <div class="aud-row"><span class="aud-key">Best product for them</span><span class="aud-val">£27–£67 programs</span></div>
        <div class="aud-row"><span class="aud-key">Volume needed</span><span class="aud-val mid">High (passive income)</span></div>
        <div class="aud-row"><span class="aud-key">Content style</span><span class="aud-val">Technical, fight-specific</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="aud-card">
      <div class="aud-header athlete">
        <div class="aud-icon">🏉</div>
        <div class="aud-name">General Athletes</div>
        <div class="aud-role">Revenue Engine</div>
      </div>
      <div class="aud-body">
        <div class="aud-row"><span class="aud-key">Role</span><span class="aud-key" style="color:var(--teal);font-weight:700">Primary Revenue Target</span></div>
        <div class="aud-row"><span class="aud-key">Willingness to pay</span><span class="aud-val pay">£250–£450/mo</span></div>
        <div class="aud-row"><span class="aud-key">Best product for them</span><span class="aud-val">1:2:1 coaching</span></div>
        <div class="aud-row"><span class="aud-key">Volume needed</span><span class="aud-val" style="color:var(--green)">Low (5–6 clients)</span></div>
        <div class="aud-row"><span class="aud-key">Content style</span><span class="aud-val">"Train like an athlete"</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Revenue Model -->
  <div class="rev-section">
    <div class="rev-section-header">▸ Reverse-Engineered Revenue Mix</div>
    <div class="rev-grid">
      <div class="rev-item">
        <div class="rev-who">General Athletes</div>
        <div class="rev-product">1:2:1 Online Coaching</div>
        <div class="rev-desc">Rugby, football, cycling, triathlon. 3-month min. These clients stay 6–12 months when results come.</div>
        <div class="rev-math">£350/mo × 5 clients</div>
        <div class="rev-subtotal">£1,750</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rev-item">
        <div class="rev-who">Aspiring S&C Coaches</div>
        <div class="rev-product">Coach Mentoring</div>
        <div class="rev-desc">Your easiest close. They follow you, they want what you have. 1hr call/week + async support.</div>
        <div class="rev-math">£500/mo × 2 mentees</div>
        <div class="rev-subtotal">£1,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rev-item">
        <div class="rev-who">Combat Athletes (passive)</div>
        <div class="rev-product">Off-the-Shelf Programs</div>
        <div class="rev-desc">Lower price point, no time cost. Your 60k audience converts here. Volume play, not revenue core.</div>
        <div class="rev-math">£37 avg × 20 sales</div>
        <div class="rev-subtotal">£740</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="rev-footer">
      <div class="rev-note">5 coaching clients + 2 mentees + passive programs</div>
      <div class="rev-total-big">£3,490/mo</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Lead Gen -->
  <div class="leadgen">
    <div style="font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--teal);margin-bottom:8px;">▸ Qualified Lead Generation — Your Biggest Fix</div>
    <div class="section-title">Where to Find Athletes Who Pay</div>
    <div class="section-sub">Stop waiting for leads to come to you. These are the 4 channels that reach higher-income athletes actively.</div>

    <div class="channels">
      <div class="channel">
        <div class="ch-top">
          <div class="ch-icon ig">🔥</div>
          <div class="ch-name">Instagram (Pivot)</div>
          <div class="ch-tag hot">Do Now</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ch-body">Keep posting fight content but <strong>add 2 posts/week targeting general athletes</strong>. "Train like a fighter" hooks attract high-income athletes while keeping fighters engaged. DM automation captures both.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="channel">
        <div class="ch-top">
          <div class="ch-icon li">💼</div>
          <div class="ch-name">LinkedIn</div>
          <div class="ch-tag new">Untapped</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ch-body"><strong>This is where your paying clients live.</strong> Corporate athletes, managers, 30–45yo ex-sport professionals. Post 3x/week: "Why your gym routine isn't athletic conditioning." Direct DM outreach to rugby/football club members.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="channel">
        <div class="ch-top">
          <div class="ch-icon ref">🤝</div>
          <div class="ch-name">In-Person Network</div>
          <div class="ch-tag warm">Fastest Win</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ch-body">You've coached general pop in person. <strong>Contact every past client this week.</strong> Offer them a free online audit call. These are warm leads who already know your quality. Easiest first clients.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="channel">
        <div class="ch-top">
          <div class="ch-icon yt">📧</div>
          <div class="ch-name">DM Qualification Flow</div>
          <div class="ch-tag hot">Do Now</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ch-body">ManyChat keyword trigger → lead magnet → <strong>3 qualifying questions</strong> (sport? goal? invested in coaching before?). Anyone who answers all 3 is a hot lead. Book them on Calendly. This filters time-wasters automatically.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Phases -->
  <div class="phases-label">▸ Phase-by-Phase Plan to £3,500/mo</div>
  <div class="phases">

    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-hdr open" onclick="toggle(this)">
        <div class="ph-n">1</div>
        <div class="ph-i">
          <div class="ph-when">March · Weeks 1–3 · Start Immediately</div>
          <div class="ph-title">Warm Outreach + Pivot Content</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ph-rev">Target: £500</div>
        <div class="ph-chev">▾</div>
      </div>
      <div class="phase-body open">
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Contact every past in-person client this week</strong><span>You have real credibility with these people. Message them: "I've moved online — offering free 20-min performance audits this month." These are your fastest first coaching clients. Don't skip this.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-fire">Fastest Win</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Rewrite IG bio for dual audience</strong><span>"S&C Coach · Helping athletes & fighters build performance-ready strength · Programs + 1:2:1 coaching 👇" — Calendly link. Speaks to both audiences without alienating either.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-fire">Fastest Win</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Create LinkedIn profile from scratch (2hrs)</strong><span>Headline: "S&C Coach helping athletes perform better | Combat sports specialist | Online coaching." Post your first piece: "What fighters understand about strength that most athletes don't." This attracts exactly the right people.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-lead">Lead Gen</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Post 2 "train like an athlete" pieces on IG this week</strong><span>Hook: "You don't need to fight to train like a fighter." Or: "The conditioning method combat sports athletes use that transforms general performance." These attract your paying audience while your fight content keeps credibility.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-cont">Content</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Lower your program prices for fighters (£27–£47)</strong><span>Stop fighting the market. At £37 you need 20 sales for £740 — very achievable from 60k. Remove friction entirely. These fund your business while coaching clients are the profit.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-rev">Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Set up ManyChat with dual keyword triggers</strong><span>"FIGHTER" triggers → fight program offer. "ATHLETE" triggers → coaching audit booking. One automation, two audiences, running 24/7 from your existing content.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-sys">System</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-hdr" onclick="toggle(this)">
        <div class="ph-n">2</div>
        <div class="ph-i">
          <div class="ph-when">April · Weeks 4–7</div>
          <div class="ph-title">Sign First Clients + Launch Mentoring</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ph-rev">Target: £1,500</div>
        <div class="ph-chev">▾</div>
      </div>
      <div class="phase-body">
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Sign 2–3 general athlete coaching clients (£300–£350/mo)</strong><span>From your in-person network outreach and LinkedIn DMs. Offer a 2-week trial at £99 if they're hesitant — most convert. 3-month minimum commitment from day one.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-rev">Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Post 3 pieces of "aspiring coach" content on IG + LinkedIn</strong><span>"What I wish I knew before coaching online." "How I went from in-person to online S&C." These attract your mentoring clients. Your 60k fighter audience includes hundreds of aspiring coaches already.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-cont">Content</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Sign first mentoring client at £500/mo</strong><span>1hr/week call + WhatsApp async support. Cover: online programming, client management, content strategy, business setup. This is 4hrs/month of your time for £500. Your highest ROI offer.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-rev">Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Build a simple coaching application page (Tally.so free)</strong><span>3 questions: What sport do you play? What's your performance goal? Have you invested in a coach before? Anyone who fills this in is qualified. Link this from your bio and every coaching CTA.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-lead">Lead Gen</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>DM 20 LinkedIn connections who match your ideal client</strong><span>Search: rugby, football, triathlon, cycling. Message: "Noticed you're into [sport] — I work with athletes on S&C for performance. Happy to share a free audit if useful." No pitch. Just value.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-lead">Lead Gen</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-hdr" onclick="toggle(this)">
        <div class="ph-n">3</div>
        <div class="ph-i">
          <div class="ph-when">May · Weeks 8–11</div>
          <div class="ph-title">Scale to 4 Clients + Build Systems</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ph-rev">Target: £2,500</div>
        <div class="ph-chev">▾</div>
      </div>
      <div class="phase-body">
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Scale coaching to 4–5 clients at full £350/mo</strong><span>By now you have proof, testimonials, and a working lead system. No more founding discounts. Your application page pre-qualifies so you only speak to serious people.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-rev">Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Add a "Train Like a Fighter" general athlete program (£97)</strong><span>Bridges both audiences. Fighters can't afford coaching but general athletes will pay £97 for the fighter aesthetic. Repurpose your existing programming knowledge. 1 weekend to build.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-rev">Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Systematise your coaching delivery (max 1hr/client/week)</strong><span>Notion check-in template + weekly video message (Loom, 5 mins) + WhatsApp for questions. Scalable, personal, zero admin bloat. You must protect your time as revenue grows.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-sys">System</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Collect 3+ detailed client testimonials (video preferred)</strong><span>Prompt them: "What were you struggling with, what changed, and what would you tell someone thinking about coaching?" Post one per week as content. Each testimonial generates 2–3 enquiries.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-cont">Content</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Set up 3-email post-call follow-up (MailerLite free)</strong><span>Email 1: audit recap + offer (same day). Email 2: case study 48hrs later. Email 3: final nudge day 5. Most sales happen in follow-up — without this you're leaving 40% of revenue on the table.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-sys">System</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-hdr" onclick="toggle(this)">
        <div class="ph-n">4</div>
        <div class="ph-i">
          <div class="ph-when">June–July · Weeks 12–16</div>
          <div class="ph-title">Hit £3,500 + Automate Everything</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ph-rev">Target: £3,500+</div>
        <div class="ph-chev">▾</div>
      </div>
      <div class="phase-body">
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Fill coaching roster to 5 clients at £350/mo = £1,750 recurring</strong><span>Lead system is running. LinkedIn + IG automation + referrals from existing clients generate 3–5 enquiries/week. Your application page filters to only qualified conversations.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-rev">Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Sign 2nd mentoring client = £1,000/mo recurring from mentoring</strong><span>Combined with coaching: £2,750/mo recurring before any program sales. You're 75% of the way to target before you sell a single program.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-rev">Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Automate program upsell sequence for fighter audience</strong><span>Anyone who buys a program enters a 4-email sequence: deliver → value add → "Train Like a Fighter" upsell → coaching pitch. Your 60k audience becomes a passive income machine.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-sys">System</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Pre-sell your S&C Coach course (validate before building)</strong><span>Post: "Building a course for aspiring S&C coaches. 10 founding spots at £197." If 10 people buy = £1,970 + proof the course is worth building. Never build before you validate.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-rev">Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="task" onclick="tick(this)">
          <div class="cb"></div>
          <div class="task-copy"><strong>Review, document what worked, set £6,000/mo Q4 target</strong><span>By July you have: recurring coaching revenue, mentoring income, passive program sales, a validated course, and systems running without you. July is the launchpad — not the finish line.</span></div>
          <div class="badge b-sys">System</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- Progress -->
  <div class="prog-wrap">
    <div class="prog-meta">
      <div>Overall progress</div>
      <div><span id="dc">0</span> / <span id="tc">0</span> tasks completed</div>
    </div>
    <div class="track"><div class="fill" id="fb"></div></div>
  </div>

</div>

<script>
  function toggle(hdr) {
    hdr.classList.toggle('open');
    hdr.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open');
  }

  function tick(row) {
    row.querySelector('.cb').classList.toggle('ticked');
    row.classList.toggle('done');
    update();
  }

  function update() {
    const total = document.querySelectorAll('.task').length;
    const done = document.querySelectorAll('.cb.ticked').length;
    document.getElementById('dc').textContent = done;
    document.getElementById('tc').textContent = total;
    document.getElementById('fb').style.width = (done / total * 100) + '%';
  }

  window.addEventListener('load', () => {
    update();
    document.querySelectorAll('.phase-hdr')[0].classList.add('open');
    document.querySelectorAll('.phase-body')[0].classList.add('open');
  });
</script>
</body>
</html>
